cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 

1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the downlink performance of 5G network architectures, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper discusses the SIR distribution and average Shannon and outage rates, which are related to information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a comparative modeling for two systems and leverages stochastic geometry results and large-system analytical tool, which are related to systems and control. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the spectral and energy efficiency of two 5G network architectures, which are related to multimedia applications. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - Although less likely, the paper may also fall under the scope of hardware architecture as it discusses the optimal design of practical 5G networks.
